commit.message: Bump version to 0.16.2.0
Attempt to update CI

Add type signature to bin (fixes #202)

See also. https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/issues/23224
Add serialization tests for negative binomial distribution.
Add tests for negative binomial.

Negative Binomial:  Implement.

The implementation is based on that of the binomial distribution.
Fix typos

Geometric distribution:  Improve accuracy for large s.

When the success probability parameter s >= 0.5, the approach using
log1p and similar functions is not as accurate as the previously used
direct computation.  This is because in that case, the intermediate
quantity 1 - s can be computed without rounding error.

So we now use the direct computation for s >= 0.5 and the log1p approach
for s < 0.5.

With this change, the relative error seems to be < 1e-14 for s >= 0.5.

Geometric: Fix the tests.

Also exclude the choice p = 0 in the QC.Arbitrary instances.

geometric:  Reject invalid parameter choice p = 0.

Geometric random variables exist only for p > 0; thus p = 0 should be
disallowed.

Geometric distribution:  improve accuracy.

Improve accuracy of the probability mass function and of the entropy
formula.

commit.message:
ExactDistribution Tests:  Tighten tolerance for geometric distribution.

Reduce the tolerance level from 10^-12 to 10^-13; this passes with the
new implementation, but 10^-14 does not currently.

ExactDistribution:  New tests comparing to exact values.

These tests compares probability mass functions, cumulative distribution
and complement of the cumulative distribution to exact values as
computed with rational arithmetic.

This is applicable only to distributions which can be computed in
rational arithmetic.
Correct typos & reword a little.

FromSample:  Revise documentation.

Revise the documentation of the type class and some instances to better
reflect the intent that a fitted distribution should be returned
whenever it is reasonably possible to do so.

For Laplace, remove the comment about checking for the distribution
since it may be misleading.  Instead summarize what quantities are used
for the estimate.

Exponential Distribution:  Fix fromSample, take 2.

There were a number of errors in the fromSample function for exponential
distributions.

First, the formula was wrong:  the exponential distribution is here
parametrized by the rate, and not by the mean.  So, e.g. if you fed it
samples from an (ED 2.0) it would return you something close to an (ED
0.5) instead.

Second, it rejected any sample that had negative values in it.  This is
not helpful: While it's correct that exact exponential variates cannot
be negative, real-world samples can be noisy and may contain
negative data points.

Hypergeometric:  Implement accurate complCumulative.

The implementation of complCumulative was missing, reverting to the
default implementation of 1 - cumulative;  which results in accuracy
loss when cumulative is close to 1.

The new implementation of complCumulative is naive, but in line with the
implementation of cumulative.

Also, fix spaces in error message related to wrong parameter selection.

Binomial:  Implement more accurate complCumulative.

The previous implementation was simply 1 - cumulative, with the obvious
accuracy problems when the the cumulative value is close to 1.  The new
implementation uses the symmetry of the incomplete Beta function to achieve
more accurate numbers.

Also, remove stale comment.
Really fix bug
